 Students were evacuated [from] the Sanlam Student Village where the fire had got dangerously close and returned when the fire was extinguished said NMMU spokeswoman Zandile Mbabela. Nelson Mandela Metropolitan University has cancelled classes at three of its campuses for Wednesday after raging veld fires in Summerstrand overnight affected large parts of the campuses. Read more here: http://bit.ly/2mc1l9WPosted by HeraldLIVE - Port Elizabeth on Tuesday, February 28, 2017Nelson Mandela Metropolitan University has cancelled classes at three of its campuses for Wednesday after raging veld fires in Summerstrand overnight affected large parts of the campuses. Read more here: http://bit.ly/2mc1l9WPosted by HeraldLIVE - Port Elizabeth on Tuesday, February 28, 2017The North South and CSIR campuses were affected. Firefighters worked through the night trying to contain the fire. Fortunately nobody was hurt. Mbabela said the situation was being monitored for any possible flare-ups. TMG Digital/HeraldLIVE